CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 9, 1946, pg. 5, reads: "Election Day Highlights - Election day Tuesday, which marked the Republican landslide in Pennsylvania was a red letter day for Mr. and Mrs. John Q. Public. Top photo shows Dr. A. J. Kyles, stromy [sic?] political figure of the '30s and County Detective Walter Rainey discussing who will be 'merged and purged.'... - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Dr. A. J. Kyles and county detective Walter C. Rainey, posed in front of Kathleen's Beauty Salon, Hill District
